text.section:
"Precious metal object" means:
a precious metal that is:
gold;
iridium;
palladium;
platinum; or
silver;
a precious or semiprecious stone, or a pearl, that is or appears to have been attached to or inlaid in a precious metal listed in paragraph (1) of this subsection or any alloy of a precious metal; or
an object that is composed of a precious metal listed in paragraph (1) of this subsection or any alloy of a precious metal if:
the market value of the metal in the object lies principally in its precious metal component; or
at least 25% of the weight of the object is precious metal.
